{"key":"processedPost-9684176","value":{"id":9684176,"first":9677523,"last":9684273,"when":1233017708,"utime":"01/27/09 02:55 AM","content":"The round spots are metabolites.&nbsp; The finer fibers are part of the mycelium.&nbsp; Rhizomorphs are actually collections of thousands of smaller strands, some of which branch out as the mycelium 'feels' its way.&nbsp; The metabolites serve to break down the substrate and neutralize competitors in advance of the main 'army'.<br /><br />If your camera has a usb output, you can connect it to your computer and make time lapse videos of the mycelium colonizing the petri dish, and you can see the metabolites as they're excreted.&nbsp; Download <i>Dorgem</i> to take the pictures, and a program such as <i>Make AVI</i> to put all the jpegs together into a video.<br />RR","title":"Re: Contamination with rhizo growth"}}